2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper draws a comparison between CNNs and communication systems, which involves the transmission and processing of information, making this sub-category a likely fit.
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper analyzes the working mechanism of CNNs and their relation to communication systems, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the interpretability of CNNs, which is a key aspect of machine learning.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper draws a comparison between CNNs and communication systems, which can be seen as a control system, making this sub-category a possible fit.
